tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quality_control_data_3d_printed_parts (
    part_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    part_name VARCHAR(50),
    inspection_date TIMESTAMP,
    dimensions_3d_printed DECIMAL(10,2),
    inspector_name VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Parts (
  part_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  part_name VARCHAR(255),
  material VARCHAR(50),
  printer_model VARCHAR(100),
  production_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Inspections (
  inspection_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  part_id INT REFERENCES Parts(part_id),
  inspection_date DATE,
  inspector_name VARCHAR(50),
  pass BOOLEAN
);
CREATE TABLE PartQualityControl (id INT, part_name VARCHAR(255), inspection_date DATE, inspector_name VARCHAR(255), inspection_result BOOLEAN);
CREATE TABLE PartGeometry (id INT, part_name VARCHAR(255), geometry_data JSONB);
CREATE TABLE InspectionTools (id INT, tool_name VARCHAR(255), manufacturer VARCHAR(255), calibration_date DATE);
CREATE TABLE PartImages (id INT, part_name VARCHAR(255), image_url VARCHAR(255), image_description TEXT);

CREATE TABLE PartMeasurements (
    measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    part_id INT,
    dimension_name STRING,
    dimension_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (part_id) REFERENCES 3DPrintedParts(part_id)
);

CREATE TABLE InspectionLogs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    part_id INT,
    inspector_id INT,
    inspection_date DATE,
    result VARCHAR,
    FOREIGN KEY (part_id) REFERENCES 3DPrintedParts(part_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (inspector_id) REFERENCES Inspectors(inspector_id)
);
